= page_header('About Jessica')

.row.content
  .span5
    %p
      Jessica Rowe, LCSW-C, is a lifelong resident of Howard County, Maryland.  She earned a BA from Dickinson College and a Master of Social Work from the University of Michigan, with a Certificate in Aging.  Jessica has worked for 30 years in the field of aging, providing services to older adults and their families in Central Maryland. 

    %p
      Jessica has expertise in guiding families through complex decisions through her work with non-profits, a concierge health advisory, and in private practice.  She is deeply compassionate and fully devoted to the needs of older adults.  She is particularly sensitive to the concerns of caregivers.

  .span3
    .right
      = image_tag 'jessica.png', size: '150x150'

.row
  .span8
    %p
      Jessica is a licensed clinical social worker in Maryland (LCSW-C).  She is currently an instructor at the University of Maryland School of Social Work teaching graduate students specializing in the field of aging. 

    %p
      She is a member of the National Association of Social Workers (NASW), the National Association of Professional Geriatric Care Managers (NAPGCM), and the Coalition of Geriatric Services (COGS). Through NASW she is a Certified Advanced Social Work Case Manager 
      (C- ASWCM).

